<item>
            <title>[SWF-206] Usage of InheritableThreadLocal invites ClassLoader reference leaks</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SWF-206</link>
                <project id="10050" key="SWF">Spring Web Flow</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;An almost identical issue was recently fixed by Juergen for Spring core 2.0.1 / 1.2.9: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2258&quot; title=&quot;Use of InheritableThreadLocal creates leak for newly created background threads&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2258&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2258&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Usage of InheritableThreadLocal in ExternalContextHolder is the same thing. Instead of duplicating the reasons why you should (almost) never use InheritableThreadLocal in a J2EE environment, I&apos;ll just point you to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2258&quot; title=&quot;Use of InheritableThreadLocal creates leak for newly created background threads&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2258&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2258&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not asking to unconditionally remove this, just make it configurable with a safe default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
